{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Our work provides critical new insights regarding the causal effects of LLMs on collaborative innovation and provides a much-needed framework for understanding what to look for in an innovation task while you are trying to predict the impact of LLMs on that task, a question marked with contrasting outcomes in literature.",
    "As LLM adoption accelerates among programmers, understanding these technologies' impact on innovation becomes critical.",
    "While existing research has documented how LLMs enhance individual productivity in guided environments (Brynjolfsson et al. 2025; Peng et al. 2023) or voluntary environments (Song et al. 2024, Hoffmann et al. 2024), our study extends this understanding to voluntary collaborative settings characterized by unguided contributions from highly skilled participants.",
    "Open-source software development represents a unique innovation context that differs fundamentally from organizational settings.",
    "It is characterized by rapid evolution (Paulson et al. 2004), self-selection of contributors based on perceived values (Shah 2006; Miric and Jeppesen 2023), and a blend of capability innovation (expanding what software can do) and iterative innovation (enhancing existing functionality quality)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "While existing research has documented how LLMs enhance individual productivity in guided environments (Brynjolfsson et al. 2025; Peng et al. 2023) or voluntary environments (Song et al. 2024, Hoffmann et al. 2024), our study extends this understanding to voluntary collaborative settings characterized by unguided contributions from highly skilled participants.",
    "It is characterized by rapid evolution (Paulson et al. 2004), self-selection of contributors based on perceived values (Shah 2006; Miric and Jeppesen 2023), and a blend of capability innovation (expanding what software can do) and iterative innovation (enhancing existing functionality quality)."
